ADDITIONAL TERMS — TEMPLATE-SPECIFIC USAGE

This MIT License covers the source code, scenes, scripts, shaders and project
configuration files of the "Block Puzzle Template". The following clarifies
how the MIT permissions apply to a *template* sold as a development asset:

  * YOU MAY use this template to build commercial or free games, modify any
    part of it, ship the resulting game on any platform (desktop, mobile,
    web, console) without royalties or attribution.

  * YOU MAY publish modified copies of the template internally within your
    studio, share it with collaborators on a project, and version-control
    it however you like.

  * YOU MAY NOT, however, repackage and resell this project itself as a
    template, asset pack, starter kit, or any equivalent product offered to
    third parties for them to build their own games on top of. One purchase
    grants you the right to use the template across all of your own
    projects — not to redistribute the template as your own.

The fonts shipped under "Assets/Fonts/" (Alegreya by Juan Pablo del Peral)
are released under the SIL Open Font License, version 1.1 — see "OFL.txt"
in the project root for the full text. The font may be embedded in your
exported games freely, including for commercial use.

Any other third-party assets the buyer drops into the project (icons,
audio, textures) are governed by their own licenses; the buyer is
responsible for verifying and respecting them.
